                            <comment id="18517" author="jcsahnwaldt" created="Tue, 11 Jul 2006 02:54:43 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Running the attached file with java -Dfile.encoding=ISO-8859-1 PropertiesEditorTest will print&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;continent equal? true&lt;br/&gt;
country equal? true&lt;br/&gt;
city equal? true&lt;br/&gt;
name equal? true&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Running the attached file with java -Dfile.encoding=UTF-8 PropertiesEditorTest will print&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;continent equal? true&lt;br/&gt;
country equal? false&lt;br/&gt;
city equal? false&lt;br/&gt;
name equal? false&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="18944" author="jcsahnwaldt" created="Mon, 7 Aug 2006 23:09:14 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Any news on this one? Maybe my test case wasn&apos;t entirely clear. I don&apos;t know how else to demonstrate the bug...&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Anyway, here&apos;s a patch that replaces getBytes() with getBytes(&quot;ISO-8859-1&quot;) in PropertiesEditor.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="18945" author="springboy" created="Tue, 8 Aug 2006 00:09:49 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Hi Christopher&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Fixed. Thanks for spotting this and taking the time to write a test case and a patch.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Cheers&lt;br/&gt;
Rick&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
